  "texts": [
    "This corresponds to the fact that one cannot have a 2-charge in which induced symmetry is both charged under the localized symmetry and also sources the localized symmetry.Pairing of 2-charges.",
    "Note that one can obtain a surface operator O ′ 2 carrying a 2charge having property (97) from a surface operator O 2 carrying 2-charge having property (96) by gauging the localized 2 0-form symmetry of O 2.",
    "After the gauging procedure we obtain a dual 2 0-form localized symmetry on O ′ 2.",
    "The local operator generating the induced 2 1-form symmetry is charged under the original localized 2, and so becomes a twisted sector local operator for the dual 2.",
    "Similarly, one can obtain O 2 from O ′ 2 by gauging the localized 2 0-form symmetry of O ′ 2."
